{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"flldfw2rqdq6xgicyajf7hh","title":"Training Scrum Agile-Transformation","desc":"","updated":1651176390411,"created":1651157092370,"custom":{},"fname":"training.pluralsight.scrum.agile-transformation","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"meetings"},"contentHash":"877d842149cdf63e64a850b7e71c12be","links":[{"from":{"fname":"training.pluralsight.scrum.collaboration-and-self-management-in-agile-environments","vaultName":"meetings"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":159,"offset":159},"indent":[]},"value":"training.pluralsight.scrum.agile-transformation","alias":"Collaboration & Self Management in Agile Environments"}],"anchors":{"collaboration--self-management-in-agile-environments":{"type":"header","text":"Collaboration & Self Management in Agile Environments","value":"collaboration--self-management-in-agile-environments","line":98,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"o53wni7z258rzxtzfsshz4e","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"training-scrum-agile-transformation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#training-scrum-agile-transformation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Training Scrum Agile-Transformation</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Change is the heart of every project</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Agility is our ability to initiate and respond to change</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When processes can help, we should embrace them</p>\n<ul>\n<li>When they get in our way, we should question them to determine if they serve as important guard rails or as roadblocks </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Embrace and leverage change</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-10-49-53.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make corrections along the way</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-10-50-33.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Value is vision made real</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-10-54-13.png\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"Real artists ship.\" - Steve Jobs</p>\n</blockquote>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Be realistic and conversative in our approach to cadence delivery</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-11-05-55.png\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maximize work not done</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-11-15-24.png\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-11-17-50.png\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Team members should feel safe to speak up when they think something is wrong</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-11-19-26.png\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Scrum Master</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-34-50.png\"></li>\n<li>Servant Leadership\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-36-06.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-36-39.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Scrum Ceremonies</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-39-36.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Kanban vs. Scrum</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-40-20.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Estimation</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-46-53.png\">\n<ul>\n<li>Planning Poker\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-47-55.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>T-Shirt Sizing\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-48-25.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Backlog\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-13-51-05.png\"> </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Definition of Ready</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-06-36.png\"></li>\n<li>Be careful to not let the DoR become a phase gate, dependent upon and waiting for one thing to be finished before another can be begin</li>\n<li>Should outline best practices, <strong>not hard and fast rules</strong></li>\n<li>Avoid definitions that prvent concurrent work\n<ul>\n<li>ex. \"every new story <em>must</em> include solution architecture documentation\"</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Definitions should encourage just enough detail to do the work, not exhaustive coverage</li>\n<li>Should NOT get in the way</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>INVEST model</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-07-47.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Definition of Done</p>\n<ul>\n<li>aka \"releaseable\"</li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-13-49.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Acceptance Criteria</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-14-33.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-16-00.png\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The Sprint Backlog</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is what's being done</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Story Points</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-20-28.png\"></li>\n<li>Using velocity as a metric of the team's success is a <strong>poor practice</strong></li>\n<li>In fibonaci sequence, each # is roughly 60% greater than the previous number</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Scope</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-22-19.png\"></li>\n<li>Negotiate what needs to change and ask why</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Timeboxing</p>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-26-20.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Scrum Ceremonies</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Daily Scrum\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-27-57.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-28-34.png\"></li>\n<li>Ideally first thing in the morning</li>\n<li>3 questions:\n<ul>\n<li>What did you do?</li>\n<li>What are you doing?</li>\n<li>What's blocking you?</li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-30-11.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Sprint Planning\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-31-51.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-32-21.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-32-57.png\"></li>\n<li>Anti-patterns\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-33-48.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Sprint Review\n<ul>\n<li>Could be seen as a demo</li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-34-21.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-35-13.png\"></li>\n<li>Inspect and adapt\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-36-06.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Anti-patterns\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-36-33.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Sprint Retros\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-37-25.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-37-59.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collaboration--self-management-in-agile-environments\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#collaboration--self-management-in-agile-environments\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Collaboration &#x26; Self Management in Agile Environments</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-57-24.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-58-25.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-58-42.png\"></li>\n<li>Teams need to be self-managed\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-14-59-22.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-25-29.png\"></li>\n<li>Trust is key</li>\n<li>Respect - the whole is greater than the individual, each member has something to contribute</li>\n<li>Transparency</li>\n<li>Shared authority</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Effective Collaboration: Skills Required\n<ul>\n<li>Influencing\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-37-25.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Conflict resolution\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-38-47.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-39-10.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Open-mindedness\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-39-55.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Leveraging Agile Principles for Success\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-45-17.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Leveraging Reviews and Retros\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-15-47-38.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><img src=\"/testing-notes/assets/images/2022-04-28-16-06-28.png\"></li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/testing-notes/notes/ls4f3qbg2zr4ouhrl2f7vlz\">Collaboration and Self Management in Agile Environments</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"1x6uhn78k682w086iklq4u2","title":"Pcg B","desc":"","updated":1654031745768,"created":1654031745768,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"dpd.pcg-b","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"meetings"},"contentHash":"a9a6d9bf9896b8ede94bbf5354ea28d8","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["evbuqggehe7p06bpzwe9h64","2fmg0x6zna87hprnysjij33","tlifo8lg5le1llxel16wvwl","guh58qwgt6sb8zvlsh8otax","dn7i949uhg5olk02cobbj3h"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableExportPodV2":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart"}},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink